"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453379","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>I received no further reports relating to the flight in question.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-29T15:04:27.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453379/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453379/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Aviation: Emergencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 10 February 2016 to Question 25769, on aviation: emergencies, whether he has received recent reports of further developments relating to the unplanned emergency landing of American Airlines flight AA109 at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453380","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Government has regular discussions with Midland Expressway Limited as the operator of a key part of the country’s road network.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T14:50:13.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453380/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453380/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","M6: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with Midland Expressway on the proposed sale of the M6 Toll road.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453381","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>My Department does not hold this data, as decisions about the provision of bus services, including the frequency, the level of fares or agreed local concessions are mainly a matter for the operator concerned.</p><p> </p><p>Where there is not enough demand for a bus route to be commercially viable in its own right, all local authorities have powers to subsidise bus services, Provision of subsidised services is a matter for individual English local authorities, in the light of their other spending priorities.</p><p> </p><p>We are very aware however of the importance of bus services to local communities, and in recognition of this we were able to protect Bus Service Operators Grant funding as part of the 2015 Spending Review. We have also protected the national concessionary travel in England for the whole of this Parliament.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T16:58:30.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453381/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453381/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of bus routes that have been (a) added and (b) removed since 2010.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","27305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453382","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>There are a few towns and cities that have municipal bus operators, however no analysis has been undertaken by the Department for Transport to understand the potential benefits of those models for passengers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T17:03:03.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453382/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453382/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the potential benefits for bus passengers of municipal ownership of bus companies.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","27306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453383","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>West Midlands Rail made a submission to the Secretary of State in October 2014 to devolve rail services in the West Midlands region. The Secretary of State confirmed his support in a letter to West Midlands Rail in March 2015 for rail devolution in the West Midlands and set out the expectation that West Midlands Rail will work with the Department for Transport in developing the specification for the re-letting of the next franchise. A public consultation was launched jointly with West Midlands Rail in December 2015 to inform the specification of the next West Midlands franchise. The new West Midlands Franchise is expected to commence in October 2017.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-29T14:17:35.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453383/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453383/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Railways: Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had on devolving responsibility for rail services to the Midlands.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","27307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453384","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-24","<p>Highways England conducted a structured debrief for this incident on 10 February. This is standard practice for any serious incident. It identified a number of recommendations, which are subject to ongoing discussions with other agencies. Once agreed, they will be used as lessons learnt for the management of future incidents.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-24T16:59:13.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453384/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453384/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","M6: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment Highways England has made of the effectiveness of the response to the incident on the M6 Motorway between junctions 5 and 6 on Thursday 4 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","27356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453385","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-24","<p>The structured debrief for this incident was carried out by Highways England on 10 February and included a representative from Central Motorway Police Group.</p><p>Three recommendations relating to multi-agency coordination resulted from this meeting and Highways England will continue to work closely with these agencies to take away the lessons learned.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-24T17:11:06.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453385/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453385/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","M6: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the (a) adequacy and (b) effectiveness of the level of co-operation between local authorities, the emergency services and Highways England in connection with the incident on the M6 Motorway between junctions 5 and 6 on Thursday 4 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","27355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453386","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>HS2 Ltd is already undertaking environmental surveys, meeting communities and carrying out ground investigation works on the planned line of route as part of its preparation for a Phase 2a hybrid Bill.</p><p> </p><p>This early investigation and engagement will inform a draft Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) report, which we expect to publish for consultation in autumn 2016. The draft report will show the potential environmental impacts of the scheme and indicative steps to mitigate them.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","27304","2016-02-29T15:53:01.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453386/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453386/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he will issue the draft environmental statement on Phase 2 of High Speed Two (Fradley to Crewe).","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","27303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453387","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>HS2 Ltd is already undertaking environmental surveys, meeting communities and carrying out ground investigation works on the planned line of route as part of its preparation for a Phase 2a hybrid Bill.</p><p> </p><p>This early investigation and engagement will inform a draft Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) report, which we expect to publish for consultation in autumn 2016. The draft report will show the potential environmental impacts of the scheme and indicative steps to mitigate them.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","27303","2016-02-29T15:53:01.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453387/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453387/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what arrangements are being made for public consultation on the draft environmental statement for Phase Two of High Speed 2 (Fradley to Crewe).","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","27304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453388","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>a) Public weighbridges are regulated under the Weights and Measures Act 1985 and the Non Automatic Weighing Instrument Regulations 2000. It is the responsibility of the owner of the instrument to ensure that it is maintained and continues to operate in line with the legal requirements for accuracy. Local Weights and Measures Authorities (LWMAs) are responsible for enforcement of weights and measures requirements and undertake enforcement using a risk based approach. The National Measurement and Regulation Office (NMRO) issues risk ratings for equipment for use by LWMAs which is updated each year and have rated weighbridges as high risk equipment.</p><p> </p><p>b) The operation of public weighbridges is a commercial service and their location will be a commercial decision for the operators concerned.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-02-29T11:20:37.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453388/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453388/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-19","Axle Weights: Weighing Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to ensure the (a) maintenance of and (b) appropriate location for public weighbridges.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453389","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>This information is not held centrally by the Department but each Local Weights and Measures Authority will have current information as they are responsible under Section 18 of the Weights and Measures Act 1985 for the issuing of certificates to public weighbridge operators. Information on the current location of individual public weighbridges can be found on Local Authorities’ websites from the following link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/find-weighbridge" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/find-weighbridge</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-02-29T11:21:24.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453389/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453389/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-19","Axle Weights: Weighing Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the number of operational public weighbridges was by region in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453390","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>I believe the emergency landing in question actually took place on 25 January. In accordance with EU Regulation 376/2014, safety-related events which endanger or which, if not corrected or addressed, could endanger an aircraft, its occupants or any other person have to be reported to the Civil Aviation Authority. Consequently the CAA has received a report, and will be reviewing the contents in accordance with the requirements of the Regulation.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-29T15:18:31.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453390/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453390/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Aviation: Emergencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what reports he has received of an emergency landing in Abuja by British Airways flight BA59 from Heathrow to Cape Town on 29 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453391","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>The two projects referred to in Question 26148 are:</p><p> </p><p><strong>A63 Castle Street: </strong> this has a commitment to be complete by March 2021 but the current forecast is for August 2021.</p><p> </p><p>The decision to defer was to avoid construction taking place during the year of culture.</p><p> </p><p><strong>A30 Temple to Carblake</strong></p><p> </p><p>This is being delivered by Cornwall County Council: This was originally due to Open for traffic in December 2016, although we understand from Cornwall County Council that current forecast is February 2017.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T16:50:54.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453391/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453391/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Roads: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 15 February 2016 to Question 26148, on roads: investment, which two projects are not progressing on or ahead of schedule; and when those projects are now expected to be completed.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453392","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>The last Government announced plans for a new grant to support plug-in motorcycles on 27 March 2015. Since then, the Office for Low Emission Vehicles has answered 38 items of correspondence from 20 members of the public on this issue.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T16:54:35.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453392/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453392/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Electric Vehicles: Motorcycles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 15 February 2016 to Question 26202, how many items of correspondence his Department has received from the public on the extension of the plug-in grant for motor cycles.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453393","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>Whilst we regulate Ticket Office opening times through the Ticketing and Settlement Agreement station staffing levels are a matter for operators as we believe that railway operators themselves are best placed to determine how to meet the needs of their passengers. However, it is important that those who need assistance to travel can rely on railway staff to provide this. Each operator is required to participate in the Passenger Assist system which allows disabled passengers to book staff assistance when they require it.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise that passengers can feel very strongly about station staffing hours and we expect all operators to take on board the views of stakeholders before taking any proposal to change such hours forward.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-29T13:38:46.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453393/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453393/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Railway Stations: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of staffing of railway stations on (a) passenger safety, (b) passenger assurance, (c) safety of women passengers, (d) disabled passengers, (e) revenue protection and (f) passenger assistance.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","27577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453394","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>The safety of passengers and rail users is paramount on the railway and the Department for Transport would never do anything to put passengers at risk.</p><p> </p><p>This system has already been in safe use on almost a third of rail services in Great Britain for up to 30 years and we think that it can help to improve the service to passengers. By giving responsibility to the driver to operate the doors, the other staff on board the train could provide a better face-to-face service for passengers. Putting this in the wider context of Northern Rail services, unlike the last Northern franchise in 2004 which included limited plans to invest in services or meet demand, this new franchise will deliver more than 2,000 extra services each week, nearly a 40% increase in capacity and the complete removal of the outdated and unpopular Pacers by the end of 2019.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-29T17:10:41.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453394/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453394/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect on passenger safety of removing guards and introducing driver-controlled operation on Northern Rail services.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","27578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453395","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-29","<p>Funding through the Regional Air Connectivity Fund is now available to the 11 successful bids. The start dates of the successful routes are a matter for the airlines. Flybe have announced start dates for their air services from Norwich to Exeter and Southampton to Lyon which will commence operations in March and May respectively. Funding will only be paid to airlines upon the service being provided.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-29T15:14:53.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453395/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453395/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-19","Regional Airports: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when each allocated route under the Regional Air Connectivity Fund will be launched.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","27555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453396","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Prime Minister has a goal of increasing by 20% the number of BME students in higher education. In our new guidance to the Director of Fair Access, which we published on 11 February, we ask him to maximise the contribution of Access Agreements towards this ambition. Entry rates for 18 year olds in each ethnic group increased in 2015, reaching the highest recorded values for each group. Between 2009 and 2015, the entry rate for young people in the Black ethnic group increased by over 40 percent proportionally.</p><p>Investment by the higher education sector through Access Agreements is expected to reach £746 million in 2016/17 up from £404 million in 2009/10.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-01T16:27:36.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453396/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453396/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-19","Universities: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps the Government is taking to increase the number of BME young people in university education.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","27509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453397","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>Since the 1 April 2015 Child Maintenance Group’s Financial Investigations Unit received 2,800 referrals for investigation and 3,150 investigations were completed (including cases received prior to 1 April 2015).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Note:</p><p>1. Figures are rounded to the nearest 10</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-29T14:38:59.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453397/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453397/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many cases were being dealt with by his Department's Child Maintenance Group's Financial Investigation Unit in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","27464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453398","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>Child Maintenance Group currently has 33.01 full-time equivalent staff working within the Financial Investigations Unit.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-29T14:32:17.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453398/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453398/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Department for Work and Pensions: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time equivalent staff are employed within his Department's Child Maintenance Group's Financial Investigation Unit.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","27465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453399","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-17","<p>The information is not available in the form requested.</p>The Government’s new settlement means that EU nationals whose children live abroad will ultimately receive Child Benefit at a rate that reflects the conditions – including the standard of living and child benefit paid – of the country where their child lives. This will restore fairness to the system. Meanwhile, Child Tax Credit is being phased out, and we do not have to pay the new Universal Credit for children living in other countries. That means as Universal Credit is fully rolled out, the only benefit we will pay for children living in other Member States will be the indexed rate of Child Benefit.<p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","27574","2016-03-17T16:12:44.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453399/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453399/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-19","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was paid in (a) child tax credits and (b) child benefit for children within the European Economic Area outside the UK in the most recent period for which figures are available; and what assessment he has made of the effect on the level of such payments of proposed reforms to the payment of those benefits to such children under the terms of the renegotiation proposed by the European Council.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","27522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453400","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-24","<p>The information requested regarding how many children live in households affected by the under-occupation penalty in Merseyside and the United Kingdom is published and available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The information requested regarding the average reduction in the housing benefit award for each such household is not available; but information is available for the weekly amount of spare room reduction amount (in bands) and is published at the link below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p /><p> </p><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development. Northern Ireland statistics can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research.htm</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-02-24T11:44:14.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453400/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453400/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many children live in households affected by the under-occupancy penalty in (a) Merseyside and (b) the UK; and what the average reduction in housing benefit award was for each such household.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","27488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453401","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-25","<p>The information you have requested is currently not available.</p><p> </p><p>The department does not hold information on time taken to make a payment for jobseeker’s allowance, or employment and support allowance.</p><p>Additional breakdowns will be included in the Universal Credit official statistics as quality assurance of data from the Universal Credit systems progresses during 2016.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27490","2016-02-25T15:23:14.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453401/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453401/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453401/answer/previousversion/47005","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of new claims for universal credit were paid within 42 days of a claim being made in the most recent 12 months for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","27489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453402","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-25","<p>The information you have requested is currently not available.</p><p> </p><p>The department does not hold information on time taken to make a payment for jobseeker’s allowance, or employment and support allowance.</p><p>Additional breakdowns will be included in the Universal Credit official statistics as quality assurance of data from the Universal Credit systems progresses during 2016.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27489","2016-02-25T15:23:14.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453402/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453402/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453402/answer/previousversion/47006","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of new claims for (a) jobseeker's allowance and (b) employment and support allowance were paid within 10 days of a claim being made in the most recent 12 months for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","27490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453403","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-24","<p>The information requested is shown in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Prognosis</p></td><td><p>Support Group</p></td><td><p>Work Related Activity Group</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All</p></td><td><p>2,121,500</p></td><td><p>1,564,500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3 months</p></td><td><p>225,400</p></td><td><p>344,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6 months</p></td><td><p>475,900</p></td><td><p>334,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>12 months</p></td><td><p>339,700</p></td><td><p>226,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>18 months</p></td><td><p>272,600</p></td><td><p>152,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not for 2 years</p></td><td><p>120,500</p></td><td><p>131,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not in longer term</p></td><td><p>545,100</p></td><td><p>257,400</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-24T16:32:53.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453403/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453403/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have been placed in (a) the support group and (b) the work-related activity group with a prognosis statement of (i) three months, (ii) six months, (iii) 12 months, (iv) 18 months, (v) two years and (iv) longer than two years since the introduction of employment and support allowance.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","27486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453404","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-24","<p>The information requested is not available, as Universal Jobmatch is a self-service job posting and matching service. Outcomes of vacancies posted on the site are not monitored.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-24T12:39:24.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453404/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453404/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Vacancies: Birkenhead","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what (a) proportion of vacancies listed on Universal Jobmatch that are within 20 miles of Birkenhead are unfilled and (b) wage levels those vacancies are listed at; and for how long those vacancies have been unfilled.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","27539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453405","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-26","<p>Despite an extensive search I am afraid the Department has no trace of the letter from 20 November 2015.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, my Rt. Hon. Friend Mr Iain Duncan Smith, replied to the Rt.Hon. Member's letter of 16 December 2015 on 25 February 2016.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-02-26T14:04:22.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453405/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453405/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to reply to the letters from the hon. Member for Birkenhead (a) of 20 November 2015 on school holiday provision and (b) of 16 December 2015 on the All-Party Parliamentary Group on Hunger and Food Poverty's report of December 2014.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","27526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453406","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Government has in place a robust system for verifying that those EEA nationals claiming Child Benefit are entitled to do so under the current rules and there is a wide range of checks carried out on new and existing claims to confirm their validity.</p><p>Cases of Child Benefit fraud can be investigated by DWP and the Single Fraud Investigation Service (a partnership between DWP Fraud Investigation Service and HMRC), as part of a wider investigation of welfare benefit fraud.</p><p>HMRC therefore does not hold figures on the number of Child Benefit prosecutions of foreign nationals.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-03-14T15:18:45.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453406/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453406/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-19","Child Benefit: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many foreign nationals living in the UK have been prosecuted for a fraudulent child benefit claim for a child living in the EU.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","27517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453407","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Information requested is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-29T14:35:22.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453407/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453407/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many applications for a variation from the standard formula have been made under the 2012 statutory child maintenance scheme by (a) non-resident parents and (b) parents with care since the introduction of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","27370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453408","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-24","<p>The Department has not conducted any specific evaluation work on the use of Flexible Support Fund for single parents.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-24T12:35:42.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453408/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453408/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Flexible Support Fund: Lone Parents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) effectiveness and (b) level of use by single parents of the Jobcentre Plus Flexible Support Fund.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","27357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453409","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-24","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-24T12:30:51.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453409/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453409/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Flexible Support Fund: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much and what proportion of the Flexible Support Fund was spent on female jobseekers in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","27358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453410","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>For cases administered by the Child Support Agency, as at December 2015, the number of cases within the live caseload where the non-resident parent is self employed was 97,700. This was 7.7% of the live caseload.</p><p> </p><p>For the CMS 2012 Scheme, information on employment could currently only be provided at disproportionate cost. The Child Maintenance Service is in the process of assuring employment data and this will be available at a future date.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Note</p><ol><li>Figured rounded to nearest 100.</li><li>Figures include 1993 and 2003 Schemes.</li><li>As at December 2015, the live caseload stood at 1,268,900.</li><li>Employment status is not available for cases managed off system.</li></ol>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-29T16:00:38.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453410/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453410/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of non-resident parents within the live caseload of the (a) Child Support Agency and (b) Child Maintenance Service are self-employed.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","27368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453411","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Information requested is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>CMS has direct access to income information held by Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs (HMRC) which allows the Child Maintenance Service to capture a much wider range of income types received by non-resident parents. Therefore the definition of income within variations under the 2012 scheme of maintenance has been opened to deal with almost all additional sources of income captured by self-assessment. This is referred to as “unearned income” and captures income derived from property, savings and investments (including dividends), and other miscellaneous incomes.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-29T16:28:05.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453411/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453411/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many requests were made by his Department's Child Maintenance Group to HM Revenue and Customs for information relating to a non-resident parent's unearned income in each year since the commencement of the 2012 statutory child maintenance scheme.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","27369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453412","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>The sanctions regime has a range of safeguards for claimants, including ensuring all requirements placed on claimants are reasonable, taking into account individual capability and circumstances, such as health conditions, disability and caring responsibilities.</p><p> </p><p>A further safeguard exists so that sanctions at the same level do not increase in duration when the claimant accrues 2 or more within a two week period. This ensures claimants cannot accrue lengthy sanctions within a short period in between meetings with their work coach. We keep the sanctions process under constant review and use research analysis and insight to improve the clarity of all our products and policies.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27281","2016-02-29T16:22:06.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453412/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453412/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 16 February 2016 to Question 26169, on social security benefits: disqualification, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that safeguards to prevent the accrual of sanctions are effective.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","27280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453413","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>The sanctions regime has a range of safeguards for claimants, including ensuring all requirements placed on claimants are reasonable, taking into account individual capability and circumstances, such as health conditions, disability and caring responsibilities.</p><p> </p><p>A further safeguard exists so that sanctions at the same level do not increase in duration when the claimant accrues 2 or more within a two week period. This ensures claimants cannot accrue lengthy sanctions within a short period in between meetings with their work coach. We keep the sanctions process under constant review and use research analysis and insight to improve the clarity of all our products and policies.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27280","2016-02-29T16:22:06.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453413/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453413/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 16 February 2016 to Question 26169, on social security benefits: disqualification, what the established safeguards are which are in place to prevent the accrual of sanctions.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","27281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453414","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-29","<p>The information requested on case closure arrears is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","27440","2016-02-29T15:32:05.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453414/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/453414/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2016 to Question 24142, how much is owed in child maintenance arrears by non-resident parents whose CSA liability has ended as a result of the proactive or reactive CSA case closure process.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","27439"
