"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451881","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-25","<p>National Citizen Service (NCS) delivers value for money and the most recent independent evaluation demonstrated that for every £1 spent on NCS it generates up £3.98 of social benefits. The table below shows the average cost per NCS participant calculated as part of the published independent evaluation for each year of operation:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Average cost per participant </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>£1,553</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>£1,700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>£1,570</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>£1,538</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>Figures will be made available in the NCS 2015 evaluation report, which will be published in due course.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-02-25T14:03:41.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451881/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451881/answer","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451881/answer/previousversion/46463","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 28 January 2016 to Question 23331, what the average cost for each participant of the National Citizen Service has been in each year of its operation.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","26796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451882","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-26","<p>The Prime Minister’s office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>No staff receive a home to work travel allowance or a car allowance. Health insurance is not a benefit offered to staff however, due to a TUPE transfer where Cabinet Office brought staff in from the private sector there a smaller number of staff able to claim subsidised health insurance.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","26824","2016-02-26T14:00:33.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451882/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451882/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Cabinet Office: Fringe Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff in his Department and non-departmental public bodies receive (a) home to work travel allowance, (b) a car allowance and (c) subsidised health insurance.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","26811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451883","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>A standard disclosure clause is included in Government procurement contracts. This information is publicly available on <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-22T15:38:45.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451883/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451883/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether a standard disclosure clause is included in Government procurement contracts.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","26786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451884","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>These new measures on tax compliance, introduced in 2013, enable government departments to exercise their power to exclude firms bidding for government contracts where they have been non-compliant in meeting their legal tax obligations.</p><p>The policy is compatible with the existing procurement process and is being updated to clarify the use of mandatory and discretionary exclusion criteria, contained in the new Public Contracts Regulations 2015, concerning tax compliance.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","26788","2016-02-22T15:38:12.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451884/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451884/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the procedures set out in the procurement policy note, Measures to promote tax compliance published in February 2014.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","26787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451885","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>These new measures on tax compliance, introduced in 2013, enable government departments to exercise their power to exclude firms bidding for government contracts where they have been non-compliant in meeting their legal tax obligations.</p><p>The policy is compatible with the existing procurement process and is being updated to clarify the use of mandatory and discretionary exclusion criteria, contained in the new Public Contracts Regulations 2015, concerning tax compliance.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","26787","2016-02-22T15:38:12.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451885/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451885/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many firms have been excluded from bidding for Government contracts since the introduction of the procurement policy note, Measures to promote tax compliance published in February 2014.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","26788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451886","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-22","<p>There are no general restrictions on providing banking facilities for Muslim groups. Ministers and officials hold discussions with a wide variety of organisations in the public, private and third sectors. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on Treasury departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel%20" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-22T17:16:57.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451886/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451886/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Charities: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government has had discussions with Muslim charities on a possible restriction of banking facilities for such charities.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","26701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451887","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-26","<p>The information is not available.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","27010","2016-02-26T14:00:52.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451887/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451887/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Cabinet Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the average hourly earnings of (a) female, (b) male, (c) full-time and (d) part-time employees of his Department were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","26973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451888","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>This information is publicly available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-22T15:37:32.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451888/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451888/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-10","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many freedom of information requests were (a) granted and (b) refused by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","26963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451889","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-25","<p>This information is published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) on their website <a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk</a>. ONS figures include both the mean and median gender pay gaps for the Civil Service and HM Treasury. The ONS headline estimates are also calculated using hourly earnings excluding overtime.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-25T17:37:06.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451889/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451889/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Treasury: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average hourly earnings of (a) female, (b) male, (c) full-time and (d) part-time employees of his Department were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","26981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451890","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs publishes data on income tax liabilities which includes tax on savings:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/income-tax-liabilities-by-taxpayers-marginal-rate" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/income-tax-liabilities-by-taxpayers-marginal-rate</a></p><p> </p><p>Table 2.6 shows that total tax liabilities on savings income in 2015-16 is expected to be £2,324m. These estimates are based on the 2012-13 Survey of Personal Incomes. They are projected to 2015-16 using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s March 2015 economic and fiscal outlook.</p><p> </p><p>Savings income is not exclusively interest as it includes other forms of income such as bond yield and purchased life annuity payments.</p><p> </p><p>On 6 April 2016, a tax-free Personal Savings Allowance (PSA) will be introduced for savings income (such as interest) paid to individuals. Broadly, this means that basic rate taxpayers will be able to receive up to £1,000 of savings income, and higher rate taxpayers can receive up to £500 of savings income, without any tax being due. The PSA will not be available to any saver with additional rate income.</p><p> </p><p>No overall assessment of the implications of the tax treatment of interest payments on tax revenues, across the various taxes, is available.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-26T12:23:05.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451890/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451890/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Personal Savings: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the effects of the tax treatment of interest payments on tax revenues.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","26752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451891","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-26","<p>The information is not held in the format requested. To provide the answers would incur disproportionate cost since the prosecution and conviction data has been captured centrally in alternative categories.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-26T12:07:36.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451891/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451891/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 15 January 2016 to Question 20496, how many people were (a) prosecuted and (b) convicted of offences relating to (i) corporation tax, (ii) income tax, national insurance contributions, capital gains tax and inheritance tax and (iii) other tax-related offences in each financial year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","26742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451892","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-25","<p>The government is committed to supporting savers, and government officials meet regularly with the Chartered Institute of Payroll Professionals to discuss the role that payroll deduction can play in promoting workplace saving, particularly in relation to the credit union movement. The Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) is funding a £38m project to enable participating credit unions to expand their services to many more consumers, including to employees via workplace payroll savings. DWP is also looking into providing payroll savings facilities for their staff who are members of a credit union.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-25T17:17:50.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451892/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451892/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions his Department has had with the financial sector and employer groups on workplace money management and workplace payroll savings schemes.","false","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy","26743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451893","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-26","<p>None, with the exception of 14 employees of Infrastructure UK who retain a contractual right to receive subsidised health insurance.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-02-26T14:38:30.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451893/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451893/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","Treasury: Fringe Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many staff in his Department and non-departmental public bodies receive (a) home to work travel allowance, (b) a car allowance and (c) subsidised health insurance.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","26827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451894","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-22","<p>This level of detail is not requested on VAT returns and therefore data is not available on how much VAT was raised on (a) air source heat pumps, (b) solar panels, (c) draught shipping, (d) insulation, (e) wood fuel boilers and (f) ground source heat pumps in each of the last five years.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-22T17:25:39.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451894/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451894/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was raised from VAT on (a) air source heat pumps, (b) solar panels, (c) draught shipping, (d) insulation, (e) wood fuel boilers and (f) ground source heat pumps in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","26809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451895","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-22","<p>This level of detail is not requested on VAT returns and therefore data is not available on how much VAT was raised on (a) renovating empty buildings, (b) building conversions, (c) children’s car seats, (d) carry cots and (e) mobility aids for the elderly in each of the last five years.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-22T17:23:18.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451895/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451895/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-10","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was raised from VAT on (a) renovating empty buildings, (b) building conversions, (c) children's car seats, (d) carry cots and (e) mobility aids for the elderly in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","26808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451896","Home Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>The table below outlines the number of completed C1331 customs declaration forms received by Border Force in each of the last 5 years. This data has been drawn from basic IT systems used for management information which are not subject to internal quality checks and may be subject to change.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of completed C1331 Forms received by Border Force</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>408</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>331</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>399</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>391</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>319</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>There are no records held that could adequately answer the question of how many vessels failed to complete the C1331 form.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-02-22T16:13:01.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451896/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451896/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-10","Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many vessels (a) completed and (b) failed to complete the C1331 customs declaration form in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","26831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451897","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-25","<p>In reaching the funding decisions announced at the recent Spending Review, the Government had regard to a wide range of issues that might impact on local government over the spending period. The analysis took into account a range of financial and economic factors as well as changes in demand.</p><p>When allocating funding through the local government finance settlement, the Government has taken into account the resources available to local authorities including the ability of authorities to raise funding locally through Council Tax.</p><p>The Government has made it clear that redistribution of funding between local authorities will continue under the 100% business rates retention system, to be brought in by 2020. The redistribution system will take into account differing Council Tax bases. The Government will hold a Fair Funding Review to consider the appropriate funding needs of different types of areas.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-02-25T15:52:09.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451897/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451897/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Council Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the long-term financial sustainability of councils with low council tax bases.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","26870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451898","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Government has no plans to make local authorities merge with one another. However, the Government has been clear that it will listen to proposals made by local authorities for reform that lead to more effective governance arrangements.</p><p>We are making huge strides towards rebalancing the economy and empowering local government through the devolution of powers away from Whitehall. The strength of the devolution agenda is in its localist nature: local leaders know best what their area needs and we are committed to giving them the tools to drive growth.</p><p>The Government will undertake a review to devise a new formula to assess councils’ needs and provide fair funding for every type of local authority, ahead of the introduction of 100% business rates retention by the end of this Parliament.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-02-25T15:50:49.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451898/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451898/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Council Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to merge local authorities with a low council tax base with neighbouring higher base councils to ensure financial sustainability and service provision.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","26871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451899","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-25","<p>The Government invited areas that wanted to negotiate a deal devolving major powers to come forward with written proposals by 4 September 2015. It is for local areas to propose governance structures that are right for them, including electoral changes that are wanted locally. Discussions continue with local areas on the precise arrangements to be put in place in areas to deliver deals.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-02-25T15:48:03.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451899/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451899/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received on reducing the number of (a) metropolitan district councils and (b) councillors in metropolitan counties with a combined authority and metro mayor.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","26872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451900","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-22","<p>My Department has made clear, through planning guidance, that anaerobic digestion as a form of waste development needs to be planned for. It is for local authorities to decide on the most appropriate strategy for managing waste in their area in line with planning policy and guidance.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-02-22T16:45:20.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451900/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451900/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Anaerobic Digestion: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if his Department will provide support for producers of anaerobic digestive installations in completing planning applications for those installations.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","26766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451901","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-04","<p>The information requested is already in the public domain. The Office for National Statistics publishes average salary information for each Civil Service Department by gender, and by working pattern. These figures are published as an annual salary.</p><p>The Civil Service statistics can be found at:</p><p>http://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatistics</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-04T14:08:55.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451901/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451901/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Department for Communities and Local Government: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average hourly earnings of (a) female, (b) male, (c) full-time and (d) part-time employees of his Department were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","26974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451902","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-25","<p>Whilst this is a matter for the independent Local Government Boundary Commission for England, I understand that the Commission plan to begin a review of Manchester City Council in the summer to address high electoral variances across wards in the city.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-02-25T15:52:43.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451902/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451902/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Metropolitan Districts: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he expects the Local Government Boundary Review will next consider the (a) ward and (b) councillor arrangements in the metropolitan districts within Greater Manchester.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","26874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451903","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-22","<p>The three Northstar Venture Funds that are closed to new investments are the Proof of Concept Fund, Co Investment Fund and North East Creative Content Fund.</p><p>Each Fund was designed with an investment phase and closure/end date, specified in the fund management agreements signed at the outset.</p><p>No decision has been made to exit Northstar Ventures from teh remaining deals.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-02-22T16:50:02.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451903/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451903/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-10","Northstar Ventures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 5 February 2016 to Question 26044, which three of the five funds Northstar Ventures manages are closed to new investments; and when the decision was taken that Northstar Ventures should exit from remaining deals.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","26909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451904","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-22","<p>I understand from Ofcom that the sample surveyed in the Ofcom report ‘Telecoms infrastructure access – sample survey of duct access’, published in March 2009, provided an indicative rather than representative assessment of the potential spare capacity in BT’s ducts.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-22T12:01:50.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451904/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451904/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 5 February 2016 to Question 22981, if he will ask Ofcom to publish an assessment of whether the 26 per cent of BT's ducts identified as being empty in the report, Telecoms infrastructure access - sample survey of duct access, published in March 2009, reflected the proportion of BT's ducts that were able to have fibre blown through them without further civil works in the superfast broadband rollout.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","26900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451905","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-15","<p>The information requested is already in the public domain. The Office for National Statistics publishes average salary information for each Civil Service Department by gender, and by working pattern. These figures are published as an annual salary.</p><p>The Civil Service statistics can be found at:</p><p><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatistics" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatistics</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-15T09:01:16.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451905/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451905/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the average hourly earnings of (a) female, (b) male, (c) full-time and (d) part-time employees of his Department were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","26975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451907","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Department and the Libraries Taskforce are working with representatives of authors, publishers, public libraries, the PLR office and others, to ensure library service users have access to remote e-book lending, without charge, and to consider options to appropriately remunerate authors and other rights holders.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-22T12:00:11.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451907/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451907/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Public Libraries: Electronic Publishing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress his Department has made on working with the EU Commission on extending the Public Lending Right to e-lending in local libraries.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","26966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451908","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-24","<p>There are no staff in the Department for Culture, Media and Sport who receive a home to work travel allowance, a car allowance, and/or subsidised health insurance.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold this information for its arm’s length bodies.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-24T13:28:55.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451908/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451908/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Fringe Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many staff in his Department and non-departmental public bodies receive (a) home to work travel allowance, (b) a car allowance and (c) subsidised health insurance.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","26812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451909","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-24","<p>This Government is committed to the protection of cultural heritage from destruction overseas. That is why we secured £30m of Overseas Development Assistance from 2016 to 2020 for our newly-established Cultural Protection Fund - to create opportunities for economic development through building capacity to foster, safeguard and promote cultural heritage.</p><p>The British Museum’s Iraqi Heritage Emergency Management Programme (announced on the 28th October at the Cultural Protection Summit) is the Fund's first programme. A period of consultation is now underway with expert stakeholders working in the arts, heritage, museums and development sectors, to help determine its exact scope and identify best practice.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-24T13:32:35.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451909/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451909/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Cultural Heritage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to identify the best ways to tackle cultural heritage destruction overseas.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","26714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451910","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Fountain Cavern is not currently on the UK World Heritage Tentative List, which is the first step in the process towards World Heritage Site status. If the site wishes to progress towards World Heritage Site status in the future, it will be important for the nominators to have prepared a thorough body of research to support the application. Organisations such as the UK National Commission for UNESCO and World Heritage UK are happy to provide advice on this process.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-22T13:26:09.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451910/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451910/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Cultural Heritage: Anguilla","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will take steps to support the inclusion of the Fountain Cavern in Anguilla in the UNESCO World Heritage list.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","26712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451912","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-22","<p>We recognise that a number of definitions of physical literacy exist and are used in a variety of contexts within the sport and education sectors. Sport England and a number of national partners have developed the ‘Primary School Physical Literacy Framework’ - which can be found here - http://www.sportengland.org/media/332143/Physical-literacy-framework.pdf</p><p> </p><p>It provides a useful reference to those who deliver PE and school sport and is designed to ensure that schools provide maximum opportunity for all pupils to develop their physical literacy. In this context, physical literacy can be described as the motivation, confidence, physical competence, knowledge and understanding that provides children with the foundation for lifelong participation in physical activity.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-22T13:42:33.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451912/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451912/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Sports: Public Participation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to Sporting Future: A New Strategy for an Active Nation, published by his Department in December 2015, how his Department defines physical literacy.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","26854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451913","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-22","<p>Listed buildings are designated by the Secretary of State on the basis of their special architectural and historic interest. Other factors - including their energy efficiency - can be considered through the process of seeking listed building consent (LBC) prior to the alteration, extension or demolition of such buildings. Requests for LBC are determined by the relevant local planning authority.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-22T11:58:59.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451913/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451913/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-10","Listed Buildings: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of whether current arrangements for listed building status take account of potential measures that can be taken to improve the energy efficiency of data centres.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","26798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451914","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>Each year, a number of countries participate in training with Flag Officer Sea Training. In 2015, the following 58 countries undertook training: Albania, Australia, Austria, Azerbaijan, Bahamas, Bahrain, Bangladesh, Belize, Brunei, Canada, Chile, Colombia, Denmark, Egypt, Estonia, France, Germany, Georgia, Ghana, India, Indonesia, Ireland, Italy, Jamaica, Jordan, Kenya, Korea, Kuwait, Lebanon, Libya, Malaysia, Malta, Morocco, Mozambique, Netherlands, New Zealand, Nigeria, Norway, Oman, Pakistan, Philippines, Poland, Portugal, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Senegal, Seychelles, Singapore, Somaliland, South Africa, Trinidad and Tobago, Tunisia, Turkey, Ukraine, United Arab Emirates, Uruguay, Vietnam and Yemen.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:26:25.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451914/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451914/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Navy: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what countries take part in Flag Officer Sea Training courses for surface ships and submarines.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","26807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451915","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>Successor submarine is categorised as &quot;Production of a Platform&quot; for optimism bias purposes. In line with normal Ministry of Defence processes, the optimism bias will be addressed as part of the process of securing approval for the next investment point.</p><p>I am withholding information for the current calculations for optimism bias, as the formal internal scrutiny process has not been completed.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","26887","2016-02-22T16:23:12.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451915/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451915/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what project type his Department categorised the Successor Trident programme as for optimism bias purposes.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","26802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451916","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Government has a long-standing policy not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:07:17.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451916/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451916/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Libya: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the evidence given by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State to the Foreign Affairs Committee on 10 February 2016, how many operations UK Reaper drones have undertaken in Libyan airspace this year.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","26773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451917","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The release of the Terms of Reference for the Reaper User Group will be discussed at the next meeting from 14 to 18 March 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:38:18.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451917/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451917/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2016 to Question 24110, whether he plans to publish the terms of reference for the Reaper User Group before the Group meeting on 14 to 18 March 2016.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","26843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451918","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Ministry of Defence manages a wide range of contracts to support the Successor submarine programme. The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-22T16:27:06.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451918/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451918/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Trident Submarines: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) details of contractor, (b) scope, (c) value and (d) cost overrun from the original estimate are of contracts awarded for the Successor Trident programme.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","26801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451919","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-23","<p>With reference to the answer given by my predecessor to the hon. Member for West Bromwich East (Tom Watson) on 23 June 2014 (Official Report, column 99W) we do not distinguish between platforms with different capabilities.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-23T15:07:03.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451919/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451919/answer","Hansard Extract 23 Jun 2014 HOC 198710.docx","Hansard Extract 23 Jun 2014 HOC 198710.docx","Unmanned Air Vehicles","Unmanned Air Vehicles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451919/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2016 to Question 25293, whether his Department distinguishes between the proposed use of deployed platforms with capabilities for (a) high value targeting and (b) intelligence surveillance and reconnaissance.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","26842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451920","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence on 27 January 2016 to Question 23411.</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=23411</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-22T16:37:07.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451920/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451920/answer","20160127_23411_QnA_extract_on_Navy_Deployment[1] HOC 26711.docx","20160127_23411_QnA_extract_on_Navy_Deployment[1] HOC 26711.docx","Navy Deployment","Navy Deployment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451920/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the Strategic Defence and Security Review on the global reach of the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","26711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451921","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The potential for non-operational Armed Forces roles to be filled by civilian personnel is routinely considered under the Whole Force Approach. However, details of these changes are not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-02-22T16:37:47.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451921/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451921/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Armed Forces: Civilians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 2.2.72 of his Department's Annual Report and Accounts 2014-15, for which roles responsibility has been transferred from military to civilian personnel since 2010.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","26739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451922","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 28 January 2016 to Question 24027. The Mott MacDonald report referenced in that previous answer was an Appendix to the Ernst and Young study of February 2012.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-22T16:27:53.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451922/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451922/answer","Hansard_Extract_28_January_2016_HOC_24027[1].docx","Hansard_Extract_28_January_2016_HOC_24027[1].docx","RAF Northolt Safety","RAF Northolt Safety","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451922/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","RAF Northolt: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the report produced by Ernst and Young for his Department in February 2012 on development options and safety standards at RAF Northolt recommended that an Engineered Material Arresting System be installed at RAF Northolt; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","26744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451923","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Military Airworthiness Authorisation Forum (MAWA) improves military aviation safety, reduces military air system acquisition costs, and increases interoperability through harmonisation of military airworthiness regulations. Significant cost savings in the Eurofighter Typhoon programme are likely because of MAWA work led by the UK, and our active involvement in the MAWA Forum provides the UK a position of influence across the Military aviation community.</p><p>The helicopter training programmes carried out under the European Defence Agency include Austria, Belgium, Czech Republic, Estonia, Finland, Germany, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Netherlands, Norway, Portugal, Slovenia, Sweden, Switzerland and the UK, and have derived unprecedented levels of interoperability.</p><p>Using standard operating procedures, derived in large part from UK methods, several hundred helicopter aircrew from across Europe have been exposed to, instructed in, and are now following the same procedures as UK aircrew. This means that future operations, be it under NATO, EU, or other coalition - are being de-risked through increased ability and greater interoperability. Our forces can use other nations' helicopters safely, including for medical evacuation, confident of their in-combat ability while operating in the same manner as UK assets.</p><p>The Single European Sky and Air Traffic Management Research programme is analysing the implications for military operations of new legislation and equipment upgrade programmes supporting increased commercial aviation out to 2035.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2016-02-22T16:05:49.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451923/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451923/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Aviation: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 18 December 2015 to Question 20110, what specific benefits the UK derives from membership of (a) the European Defence Agency's Military Airworthiness Authorisation Forum, (b) European Defence Agency helicopter training programmes and (c) the Single European Sky initiative.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","26747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451924","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Royal Fleet Auxiliary, Defence Equipment and Support and the Trading Funds were included in the baseline workforce calculation.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence is managing a range of change programmes designed to deliver Defence outputs more efficiently and effectively, including Army 2020 and outsourcing logistics to Leidos. A Business Improvement Review has been set up to identify opportunities to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of support activities across Defence. This Review will look at the total shape, size and structure of our civilian workforce, the functions and processes that they are engaged in, and how those can be made more efficient.</p><p>The Department expects the civilian workforce to reduce to around 41,000 by 2020. However, the timing and reductions associated with individual programmes are still to be determined and final decisions will be subject to consultation with employee representatives, value for money considerations and, where appropriate, commercial negotiation.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","26718 ; 26719","2016-02-22T16:30:15.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451924/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451924/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-10","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 4.61 of the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, whether civilians employed by (a) the Royal Fleet Auxiliary, (b) Defence Equipment and Support and (c) trading funds are included in his Department's calculation of the size of the workforce he expects to cut by 30 per cent by the end of this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","26717"
